area_name: Lower King and Queen Seat Bouldering

content.description: Start on the small corner pocket to the left with a heel and a hand on the obvious ledge to the right. Bring the right hand up to one of 2 crimps then bump it to the really good piece of the arete on the left. Match and switch hands to continue up to the top ledge. Go left to come down and watch out for thorny bushes.
content.location: Very low on the south side of king and queen seat. Right at the end of a pseudo trail coming from the right

content.description: Start on the leftmost small nub and the arete. Move to a small crimp on a flake with the right and grab a nub on the upper part with the left. Top out at the large rail up the finishing slab.
content.location: Down and to the left of pinnacle when looking from the south. Looks like it's on a pseudo trail that leads to the south side of King and Queen Seat.
